'''Baýramaly''' (formerly '''Bayram-Ali''', {{lang-tk|Baýramaly}}) is a city of [[Turkmenistan]], a seat of [[Baýramaly District]] within [[Mary Province]]. It lies about 27&nbsp;km east of the provincial capital [[Mary, Turkmenistan|Mary]], along the main railway line from [[Ashgabat]] to [[Tashkent]]. In 2009, it had a population estimated at 88,486 (up from 43,824 in the 1989 census).<ref>[http://demoscope.ru/weekly/ssp/sng89_reg2.php Population census 1989] {{webarchive |url=https://www.webcitation.org/65CnSL6Mw?url=http://demoscope.ru/weekly/ssp/sng89_reg2.php |date=2012-02-04 }}, ''Demoscope Weekly'', No. 359-360, 1–18 January 2009 (search for Туркменская ССР) {{in lang|ru}}</ref>
The city is located in a dry [[oasis]] in the [[Murgap District|Murgab]]. It is a climatic [[spa]] and the visitors are often sent to the city for the treatment of chronic [[kidney disease]], acute forms of [[nephritis]] and [[nephrosis]], [[hypertension]], renal [[tuberculosis]] and problems of blood circulation.<ref name="Great">[http://bse.sci-lib.com/article089930.html Great Soviet Encyclopedia] {{in lang|ru}}</ref>
